triples.evidence: When these high-energy particles strike a target material, nuclear reactions occur, and radionuclides are produced.

concepts.term: cyclotrons must be located relatively close to hospitals and imaging centers

evidence: Because PET imaging requires very short-lived tracers like fluorine-18, cyclotrons must be located relatively close to hospitals and imaging centers.
<One of the most well-known examples is the production of fluorodeoxyglucose, or FDG, which is widely used in PET imaging.>
